{"type":"text","timestamp":1778630479703,"sessionID":"ses_1e15da17cffeLz9LBcQt4xg1Bj","part":{"id":"prt_e1ea34f37001EU9XHnjVcYhDiZ","messageID":"msg_e1ea2c8f9001daJQl1hDyxK3JN","sessionID":"ses_1e15da17cffeLz9LBcQt4xg1Bj","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as an EX-stage micro-optimization: share/gate control-flow target arithmetic and branch comparison so ordinary ALU/address instructions do not drag duplicate next-PC adders and branch comparators through the hot execute-stage cone.","time":{"start":1778630479671,"end":1778630479702},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0a1cc608db65e338016a03bf4f77bc819aaa6b95407364f076","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778630485186,"sessionID":"ses_1e15da17cffeLz9LBcQt4xg1Bj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_4wKIVP37ywmcQRFM0ozU4wUp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r10s0\n+title: \"Gate EX control target arithmetic\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core has already benefited from reducing unnecessary fetch-side branch target work and isolating the ALU's RV32M mux. The execute stage still unconditionally forms branch targets, JAL/JALR targets, pc+4, and branch comparison results even for ordinary ALU and load/store instructions that only need the ALU result and fall-through next PC.\n+\n+  CoreMark's hot path is dominated by integer arithmetic, address generation, and loads/stores, so pruning duplicate control-flow arithmetic from the common EX cone may improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax without changing cycle count, prediction policy, memory behavior, or the NRET=1 RVFI interface.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/ex_stage.sv so control-flow next-PC work is explicitly factored and gated. Compute pc_plus4 once, share one pc_plus_imm target for both conditional branches and JAL, compute the JALR rs1+imm target only for JALR, and only evaluate the full branch comparator case when ctrl.is_branch is set. Non-control instructions should drive resolved_next_pc directly from pc_plus4 and avoid the branch/jump target mux tree.\n+\n+  This is intentionally a narrow timing cleanup, not a new predictor or early redirect. It preserves the existing static pred_next_pc contract, EX-stage misalignment trap behavior, post-forward RVFI rs1/rs2 capture, JAL/JALR rd_wdata = pc+4, and all decoder legality invariants. The expected win is a modest Fmax lift with unchanged CoreMark IPC.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Factor EX next-PC logic around a single pc_plus4 and pc_plus_imm path, gate branch comparison by ctrl.is_branch, and avoid computing JALR target arithmetic outside actual JALR instructions while preserving RVFI pc_wdata and trap behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r10s0\n+title: \"Gate EX control target arithmetic\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core has already benefited from reducing unnecessary fetch-side branch target work and isolating the ALU's RV32M mux. The execute stage still unconditionally forms branch targets, JAL/JALR targets, pc+4, and branch comparison results even for ordinary ALU and load/store instructions that only need the ALU result and fall-through next PC.\n+\n+  CoreMark's hot path is dominated by integer arithmetic, address generation, and loads/stores, so pruning duplicate control-flow arithmetic from the common EX cone may improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax without changing cycle count, prediction policy, memory behavior, or the NRET=1 RVFI interface.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/ex_stage.sv so control-flow next-PC work is explicitly factored and gated. Compute pc_plus4 once, share one pc_plus_imm target for both conditional branches and JAL, compute the JALR rs1+imm target only for JALR, and only evaluate the full branch comparator case when ctrl.is_branch is set. Non-control instructions should drive resolved_next_pc directly from pc_plus4 and avoid the branch/jump target mux tree.\n+\n+  This is intentionally a narrow timing cleanup, not a new predictor or early redirect. It preserves the existing static pred_next_pc contract, EX-stage misalignment trap behavior, post-forward RVFI rs1/rs2 capture, JAL/JALR rd_wdata = pc+4, and all decoder legality invariants. The expected win is a modest Fmax lift with unchanged CoreMark IPC.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Factor EX next-PC logic around a single pc_plus4 and pc_plus_imm path, gate branch comparison by ctrl.is_branch, and avoid computing JALR target arithmetic outside actual JALR instructions while preserving RVFI pc_wdata and trap behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r10s0\n+title: \"Gate EX control target arithmetic\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core has already benefited from reducing unnecessary fetch-side branch target work and isolating the ALU's RV32M mux. The execute stage still unconditionally forms branch targets, JAL/JALR targets, pc+4, and branch comparison results even for ordinary ALU and load/store instructions that only need the ALU result and fall-through next PC.\n+\n+  CoreMark's hot path is dominated by integer arithmetic, address generation, and loads/stores, so pruning duplicate control-flow arithmetic from the common EX cone may improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax without changing cycle count, prediction policy, memory behavior, or the NRET=1 RVFI interface.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/ex_stage.sv so control-flow next-PC work is explicitly factored and gated. Compute pc_plus4 once, share one pc_plus_imm target for both conditional branches and JAL, compute the JALR rs1+imm target only for JALR, and only evaluate the full branch comparator case when ctrl.is_branch is set. Non-control instructions should drive resolved_next_pc directly from pc_plus4 and avoid the branch/jump target mux tree.\n+\n+  This is intentionally a narrow timing cleanup, not a new predictor or early redirect. It preserves the existing static pred_next_pc contract, EX-stage misalignment trap behavior, post-forward RVFI rs1/rs2 capture, JAL/JALR rd_wdata = pc+4, and all decoder legality invariants. The expected win is a modest Fmax lift with unchanged CoreMark IPC.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Factor EX next-PC logic around a single pc_plus4 and pc_plus_imm path, gate branch comparison by ctrl.is_branch, and avoid computing JALR target arithmetic outside actual JALR instructions while preserving RVFI pc_wdata and trap behavior.\"\n","additions":17,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778630485178,"end":1778630485182}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a1cc608db65e338016a03bf4f93b0819a9fff5b3bae86250f"}},"id":"prt_e1ea34f57001afxRaf5DZPFQeA","session