l JAL instructions: compute the J-immediate target\\nfrom the IF/ID instruction and redirect the PC before the instruction reaches EX,\\nwhile preserving the normal EX-stage JAL result and RVFI pc_wdata bookkeeping for\\nretirement. JALR and conditional branches remain EX-resolved because they require\\nregister operands or comparison results. This should reduce CoreMark cycles by\\nremoving one redirect bubble from unconditional direct jumps with minimal timing cost.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire an early JAL redirect path from decode/IF into instruction fetch and hazard flushing without changing the NRET=1 RVFI interface.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Let fetch accept an early redirect target for legal JAL so the PC updates before the existing EX-stage redirect point.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose a simple legal-JAL indication and decoded J-immediate target, reusing existing decoder and immediate generation logic.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Flush the fall-through instruction on early JAL r...","metadata":{"matches":2,"truncated":false},"title":"micro_opt|category: micro_opt|\"category\": \"micro_opt\"|category.*micro","time":{"start":1778621309647,"end":1778621309661}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_071153378d608570016a039b7d71d4819b9f5d956fee85b589"}},"id":"prt_e1e1762b0001m1uLMoqDZuipiz","sessionID":"ses_1e1e8bf73ffeVgAdU7XfSxYSQj","messageID":"msg_e1e1740ee001awUBJZldZVP1pR"}}
