{"type":"text","timestamp":1778623840741,"sessionID":"ses_1e1c2c615ffehafwE79XLz1cNv","part":{"id":"prt_e1e3e017c0011sPn4FO92zpNpa","messageID":"msg_e1e3daf3200148sYheGFWou1E0","sessionID":"ses_1e1c2c615ffehafwE79XLz1cNv","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as an ALU resource-sharing micro-opt: same RV32IM visible behavior and latency, but less parallel M-extension hardware in the EX combinational cone.","time":{"start":1778623840637,"end":1778623840739},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_04adb1499c18aea3016a03a5608754819bb34f41c20baa1223","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778623850670,"sessionID":"ses_1e1c2c615ffehafwE79XLz1cNv","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_bRjiRqXhMYNlyrjBO2fCTO4a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r4s0\n+title: Share RV32M ALU arithmetic resources\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful recent change already removed many load-use bubbles, while\n+  prior front-end and predictor additions regressed from extra control and fetch\n+  path cost. The remaining low-risk fitness opportunity is Fmax/LUT pressure in\n+  the EX-stage ALU: the current combinational ALU unconditionally forms three\n+  64-bit products and leaves separate divide/remainder expressions in the result\n+  mux even though most CoreMark instructions use the simple RV32I fast path and\n+  only occasional MUL-class operations.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Rework rtl/alu.sv so the RV32I fast ALU path is unchanged, but RV32M arithmetic\n+  is resource-shared. Use a single sign-controlled extended multiplier that\n+  covers MUL, MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU instead of computing signed*signed,\n+  unsigned*unsigned, and signed*unsigned products in parallel. Similarly factor\n+  DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU operand preparation and special-case handling so quotient\n+  and remainder selection is centralized rather than replicated per case arm.\n+\n+  This should reduce LUT use and the M-extension fan-in around the ALU output\n+  mux, improving median FPGA Fmax with essentially unchanged CoreMark cycle\n+  count. The ALTOPS formal branch must remain byte-for-byte equivalent in\n+  behavior, and the existing cocotb ALU vectors plus cosim should guard exact\n+  RV32M arithmetic semantics.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the three parallel multiplier datapaths with one signedness-controlled extended product and factor DIV/REM special-case logic into shared combinational quotient/remainder selection, preserving ALTOPS behavior.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Add or extend MULH/MULHU/MULHSU and DIV/REM edge-case vectors if needed to prove the shared arithmetic datapath preserves RV32M bit results.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r4s0\n+title: Share RV32M ALU arithmetic resources\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful recent change already removed many load-use bubbles, while\n+  prior front-end and predictor additions regressed from extra control and fetch\n+  path cost. The remaining low-risk fitness opportunity is Fmax/LUT pressure in\n+  the EX-stage ALU: the current combinational ALU unconditionally forms three\n+  64-bit products and leaves separate divide/remainder expressions in the result\n+  mux even though most CoreMark instructions use the simple RV32I fast path and\n+  only occasional MUL-class operations.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Rework rtl/alu.sv so the RV32I fast ALU path is unchanged, but RV32M arithmetic\n+  is resource-shared. Use a single sign-controlled extended multiplier that\n+  covers MUL, MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU instead of computing signed*signed