{"type":"text","timestamp":1778624673795,"sessionID":"ses_1e1b5c35affe75ZA9YOvivQFaO","part":{"id":"prt_e1e4ab735002u0aApkpFLa2NiV","messageID":"msg_e1e4a6084001m5nluIme08mbBq","sessionID":"ses_1e1b5c35affe75ZA9YOvivQFaO","type":"text","text":"The prior log rules out heavier predictor/front-end state and M-resource sharing. I’m going to write a narrow `micro_opt` hypothesis aimed at reducing FPGA reset/control cost in the register file rather than changing pipeline behavior.","time":{"start":1778624673589,"end":1778624673794},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_026f9c21ca0648c2016a03a8a17efc819582443b4aef3b0ca6","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778624681863,"sessionID":"ses_1e1b5c35affe75ZA9YOvivQFaO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_3Y6l4nPCilP8qJIsLr463AxD","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r5s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r5s0\n+title: \"Trim register file reset cost\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best design already gained IPC from static direct-control prediction and MEM-to-EX load forwarding, while recent attempts that add predictor state or reshape RV32M arithmetic hurt timing. A lower-risk remaining micro-optimization is the integer register file: it synchronously clears all 32 architectural registers on reset even though x0 is hardwired and normal RISC-V software initializes live registers before use. That reset fanout and x0 storage can cost LUT/FF resources and routing on the Tang Nano 20K without improving CoreMark's timed behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Rewrite the register file as 31 physical x1-x31 entries with x0 handled only in the read and write guards, and remove the bulk reset loop from the physical entries. Keep the same write-first bypass semantics so same-cycle WB-to-ID behavior and RVFI source data remain unchanged. This should reduce reset-net fanout, a small amount of storage/control logic, and potentially improve median Fmax without changing cycle count, memory ordering, decode legality, or the NRET=1 RVFI contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/reg_file.sv\n+    description: \"Store only x1-x31 and remove the synchronous reset sweep while preserving x0 hardwiring, write gating, and write-first read bypass behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r5s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-