{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778626145534,"sessionID":"ses_1e19fab4dffexL70OjRY7iOhuQ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_bYmqP8KNrI3NntcH2C1mAKuB","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Simplify MEM load lane mux\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core gained IPC by forwarding extended MEM-stage load data\n+  directly into EX, but that makes the MEM load extraction logic part of a hot\n+  bypass path. The existing implementation uses variable shifts and shifted\n+  byte masks for every access width, which can synthesize into a wider mux cone\n+  than the four byte lanes actually require.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Rewrite the MEM-stage byte/halfword load extraction and store-mask generation\n+  as explicit lane case statements keyed by addr[1:0] instead of variable shifts\n+  and shift-by-eight arithmetic. Keep the same misalignment gating, RVFI aligned\n+  address/mask reporting, load_fwd_data semantics, and NRET=1 top-level port set.\n+\n+  This should slightly improve median Tang Nano 20K Fmax by shortening the\n+  dmem_rdata-to-load_fwd_data-to-EX forwarding cone and simplifying store mask\n+  decode, with no cycle-count cost and far less risk than adding predictor state,\n+  changing the register file, or restructuring RV32M arithmetic.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace variable load-data shifts and shifted byte-mask generation with explicit addr[1:0] lane cases while preserving misalignment traps, RVFI masks, and MEM-to-EX load forwarding behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Simplify MEM load lane mux\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core gained IPC by forwarding extended MEM-stage load data\n+  directly into EX, but that makes the MEM load extraction logic part of a hot\n+  bypass path. The existing implementation uses variable shifts and shifted\n+  byte masks for every access width, which can synthesize into a wider mux cone\n+  than the four byte lanes actually require.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Rewrite the MEM-stage byte/halfword load extraction and store-mask generation\n+  as explicit lane case statements keyed by addr[1:0] instead of variable shifts\n+  and shift-by-eight arithmetic. Keep the same misalignment gating, RVFI aligned\n+  address/mask reporting, load_fwd_data semantics, and NRET=1 top-level port set.\n+\n+  This should slightly improve median Tang Nano 20K Fmax by shortening the\n+  dmem_rdata-to-load_fwd_data-to-EX forwarding cone and simplifying store mask\n+  decode, with no cycle-count cost and far less risk than adding predictor state,\n+  changing the register file, or restructuring RV32M arithmetic.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace variable load-data shifts and shifted byte-mask generation with explicit addr[1:0] lane cases while preserving misalignment traps, RVFI masks, and MEM-to-EX load forwarding behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-ru