{"type":"text","timestamp":1778627312690,"sessionID":"ses_1e18e19d3ffepbuaJ3c5iyfz0x","part":{"id":"prt_e1e72f8520011e02HivdNMnX5F","messageID":"msg_e1e720eaf001MbiR2A5Gk664BY","sessionID":"ses_1e18e19d3ffepbuaJ3c5iyfz0x","type":"text","text":"The strongest micro_opt candidate I see is a late-pipeline metadata trim: unlike the recent failed IF/RF/ALU/memory-mux attempts, it avoids the known hot paths and only removes unused control/branch fields carried through EX/MEM and MEM/WB. I’m writing that as a focused hypothesis now.","time":{"start":1778627311698,"end":1778627312689},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_03c30df1deb3f771016a03b2ef823c8194992f60134841bab2","phase":"commentary"}}}}
