{"type":"text","timestamp":1778630456507,"sessionID":"ses_1e15da0acffeFPSHCJ4NBp7fzq","part":{"id":"prt_e1ea2f304001YMP1QqmCv6vsLM","messageID":"msg_e1ea2abbf001recS0iaNxcc0Sr","sessionID":"ses_1e15da0acffeFPSHCJ4NBp7fzq","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a narrow structural hypothesis file now. It avoids the front-end/stateful ideas that have repeatedly regressed and targets the remaining broad EX datapath cost with a multi-cycle divider sidecar.","time":{"start":1778630456068,"end":1778630456505},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_04486db4bd0f18a2016a03bf37f6d48199b1bfbe474d07a000","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778630468723,"sessionID":"ses_1e15da0acffeFPSHCJ4NBp7fzq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_VpJERhb1le29Lxcg80tCIVUi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r10s1\n+title: \"Sidecar iterative divider\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX-stage ALU still contains full combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU\n+  operators even though CoreMark's hot timed path is dominated by loads, stores,\n+  branches, integer ALU ops, and occasional multiply. Prior structural attempts\n+  that added front-end queues, store buffering, early JALR, or register-file\n+  restructuring regressed because they added control to hot paths. Removing the\n+  rare divider/remainder cone from the single-cycle EX result path is a more\n+  localized structural change with a direct chance to improve FPGA Fmax and LUT\n+  pressure.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split RV32M division and remainder out of the combinational ALU into a small\n+  iterative divide sidecar that is only activated for DIV, DIVU, REM, and REMU.\n+  EX should hold ID/EX and suppress EX/MEM advancement while the sidecar is busy,\n+  then inject the completed quotient or remainder into the normal EX/MEM result\n+  path with the original instruction metadata intact. ADD/SUB/logic/shift,\n+  address generation, branches, jumps, and MUL/MULH variants remain one-cycle,\n+  and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS keeps its one-cycle substituted behavior. This should\n+  improve median Tang Nano 20K Fmax more than it costs IPC because real divide\n+  and remainder instructions are rare in the benchmark window.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU operators from the common combinational ALU path while preserving one-cycle RV32I, multiply, and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate and control an iterative divide sidecar, hold EX while it is busy, and route the completed divide/remainder result into the existing EX/MEM register with unchanged RVFI metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX busy stall input so divide/remainder waits freeze fetch/decode/execute without disturbing redirect, dmem-stall, or single-retire RVFI ordering semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the divider-busy stall path between EX and the hazard unit while keeping the nret=1 top-level IO unchanged.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or retain RV32M divide/remainder vectors so the sidecar still proves exact RV32IM edge-case semantics under cocotb.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r10s1\n+title: \"Sidecar iterative divider\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX-stage ALU still contains full combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU\n+  operators even though CoreMark's hot timed path is dominated by loads, stores,\n+  branches, integer ALU ops, and occasional multiply. Prior structural attempts\n+  that added front-end queues, store buffering, early JALR, or register-file\n+  restructuring regressed because they added control to hot paths. Removing the\n+  rare divider/remainder cone from the single-cycle EX result path is a more\n+  localized structural change with a direct chance to improve FPGA Fmax and LUT\n+  pressure.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split RV32M division and remainder out of the combinational ALU into a small\n+  iterative divide sidecar that is only activated for DIV, DIVU, REM, and REMU.\n+  EX should hold ID/EX and suppress EX/MEM advancement while the sidecar is busy,\n+  then inject the completed quotient or remainder into the normal EX/MEM result\n+  path with the original instruction metadata intact. ADD/SUB/logic/shift,\n+  address generation, branches, jumps, and MUL/MULH variants remain one-cycle,\n+  and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS keeps its one-cycle substituted behavior. This should\n+  improve median Tang Nano 20K Fmax more than it costs IPC because real divide\n+  and remainder instructions are rare in the benchmark window.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU operators from the common combinational ALU path while preserving one-cycle RV32I, multiply, and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate and control an iterative divide sidecar, hold EX while it is busy, and route the completed divide/remainder result into the existing EX/MEM register with unchanged RVFI metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX busy stall input so divide/remainder waits freeze fetch/decode/execute without disturbing redirect, dmem-stall, or single-retire RVFI ordering semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the divider-busy stall path between EX and the hazard unit while keeping the nret=1 top-level IO unchanged.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or retain RV32M divide/remainder vectors so the sidecar still proves exact RV32IM edge-case semantics under cocotb.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r10s1\n+title: \"Sidecar iterative divider\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX-stage ALU still contains full combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU\n+  operators even though CoreMark's hot timed path is dominated by loads, stores,\n+  branches, integer ALU ops, and occasional multiply. Prior structural attempts\n+  that added front-end queues, store buffering, early JALR, or register-file\n+  restructuring regressed because they added control to hot paths. Removing the\n+  rare divider/remainder cone from the single-cycle EX result path is a more\n+  localized structural change with a direct chance to improve FPGA Fmax and LUT\n+  pressure.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split RV32M division and remainder out of the combinational ALU into a small\n+  iterative divide sidecar that is only activated for DIV, DIVU, REM, and REMU.\n+  EX should hold ID/EX and suppress EX/MEM advancement while the sidecar is busy,\n+  then inject the completed quotient or remainder into the normal EX/MEM result\n+  path with the original instruction metadata intact. ADD/SUB/logic/shift,\n+  address generation, branches, jumps, and MUL/MULH variants remain one-cycle