:\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"category: predictor|predictor|branch|BHT|BTB|JALR|RAS|loop\",\"path\":\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments\",\"include\":\"log.jsonl\"},\"output\":\"Found 28 matches\\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl:\\n  Line 2: {\\\"id\\\": \\\"hyp-20260512-001-r1s0\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Resolve JAL one stage earlier\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"micro_opt\\\", \\\"motivation\\\": \\\"CoreMark contains frequent unconditional calls and loop-control jumps. The current\\\\npipeline treats JAL like every other control transfer and redirects from EX, so each\\\\ntaken JAL pays the same two wrong-path bubbles as a conditional branch even though\\\\nits target is fully known from the instruction bits in decode.\\\\n\\\", \\\"hypothesis\\\": {\\\"motivation\\\": \\\"CoreMark contains frequent unconditional calls and loop-control jumps. The current\\\\npipeline treats JAL like every other control transfer and redirects from EX, so each\\\\ntaken JAL pays the same two wrong-path bubbles as a conditional branch even though\\\\nits target is fully known from the instruction bits in decode.\\\\n\\\", \\\"hypothesis\\\": \\\"Add a decode/IF fast path for legal JAL instructions: compute the J-immediate target\\\\nfrom the IF/ID instruction and redirect the PC before the instruction reaches EX,\\\\nwhile preserving the normal EX-stage JAL result and RVFI pc_wdata bookkeeping for\\\\nretirement. JALR and conditional branches remain EX-resolved because they require\\\\nregister operands or comparison results. This should reduce CoreMark cycles by\\\\nremoving one redirect bubble from unconditional direct jumps with minimal timing cost.\\\\n\\\", \\\"expected_impact\\\": {\\\"fitness_delta_pct\\\": 3, \\\"confidence\\\": \\\"medium\\\"}, \\\"chang... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1778631398916,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e14ed2a4ffehDZT9w0UI0ynQN\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1eb15602001AudxStsP1AA8ga\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"3d1a5841c1551e6b829b1cd6523bc164052a80e2\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1eb12d970016L3GuHp66rXr7G\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e14ed2a4ffehDZT9w0UI0ynQN\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":40018,\"input\":24301,\"output\":204,\"reasoning\":153,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":15360}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1778631399841,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e14ed2a4ffehDZT9w0UI0ynQN\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1eb159a0001jz6nS5SRTPWyrh\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1eb15642001dTIDBO8eTMmGEA\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e14ed2a4ffehDZT9w0UI0ynQN\",\"snapshot\":\"3d1a5841c1551e6b829b1cd6523bc164052a80e2\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.log","time":{"start":1778631407423,"end":1778631407526}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04e145b0303f1df6016a03c2ef48a0819aac8ef74650ea8b3b"}},"id":"prt_e1eb1773e002sUslcb0Vgad5Ps","sessionID":"ses_1e14ed357ffeA57MiySdQujFwm","messageID":"msg_e1eb15379001e11hgzOS8L59i5"}}
