{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778631502409,"sessionID":"ses_1e14ed357ffeA57MiySdQujFwm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_lfK6R47bhmLmycC6S0PzzEfH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/schemas/hypothesis.schema.json","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/schemas/hypothesis.schema.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\",\n3:   \"type\": \"object\",\n4:   \"required\": [\"id\",\"title\",\"category\",\"motivation\",\"hypothesis\",\"expected_impact\",\"changes\"],\n5:   \"properties\": {\n6:     \"id\":       {\"type\": \"string\", \"pattern\": \"^hyp-[0-9]{8}-[0-9]{3}(-r[0-9]+s[0-9]+)?$\"},\n7:     \"title\":    {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 5},\n8:     \"category\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"micro_opt\",\"structural\",\"extension\",\"predictor\",\"memory\"]},\n9:     \"motivation\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n10:     \"hypothesis\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n11:     \"expected_impact\": {\n12:       \"type\": \"object\",\n13:       \"required\": [\"fitness_delta_pct\",\"confidence\"],\n14:       \"properties\": {\n15:         \"fitness_delta_pct\": {\"type\": \"integer\"},\n16:         \"confidence\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"low\",\"medium\",\"high\"]}\n17:       }\n18:     },\n19:     \"changes\": {\n20:       \"type\": \"array\", \"minItems\": 1,\n21:       \"items\": {\n22:         \"type\": \"object\",\n23:         \"required\": [\"file\",\"description\"],\n24:         \"properties\": {\n25:           \"file\":        {\n26:             \"type\": \"string\",\n27:             \"description\": \"Must be under rtl/ (any extension) or be a test/test_*.py cocotb suite. Anything else is rejected by the runtime sandbox check.\",\n28:             \"pattern\": \"^(rtl/[^.].*|test/test_[^/]+\\\\.py)$\"\n29:           },\n30:           \"description\": {\"type\": \"string\"}\n31:         }\n32:       }\n33:     }\n34:   }\n35: }\n\n(End of file - total 35 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\",\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"required\": [\"id\",\"title\",\"category\",\"motivation\",\"hypothesis\",\"expected_impact\",\"changes\"],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"id\":       {\"type\": \"string\", \"pattern\": \"^hyp-[0-9]{8}-[0-9]{3}(-r[0-9]+s[0-9]+)?$\"},\n    \"title\":    {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 5},\n    \"category\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"micro_opt\",\"structural\",\"extension\",\"predictor\",\"memory\"]},\n    \"motivation\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n    \"hypothesis\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"required\": [\"fitness_delta_pct\",\"confidence\"],\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": {\"type\": \"integer\"},\n        \"confidence\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"low\",\"medium\",\"high\"]}\n      }\n    },\n    \"changes\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\", \"minItems\": 1,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"schemas/hypothesis.schema.json","time":{"start":1778631502376,"end":1778631502407}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03a990bfa4cc7b05016a03c34e3f54819b88ff1b62452876dc"}},"id":"prt_e1eb2ea28001ih5zAAJRMwjJra","sessionID":"ses_1e14ed357ffeA57MiySdQujFwm","messageID":"msg_e1eb2cda9001yqpm39ueZ2F0XA"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778631502456,"sessionID":"ses_1e14ed357ffeA57MiySdQujFwm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_C1Ufu0zQb6QPNlU35Wve4cvl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-002-r11s1\n2: title: \"Skid one ALU op behind dmem stalls\"\n3: category: structural\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The current pipeline freezes every stage whenever a load or store in MEM waits for io_dmemReady. Prior structural attempts that added front-end queues or a store buffer regressed because they added broad control and memory-ordering muxes, but randomized dmem backpressure is still a direct IPC limiter. A narrower structural change can use the first blocked cycle behind a memory operation without changing prediction, memory ordering, or the NRET=1 RVFI contract.\n6: hypothesis: |\n7:   Add a one-entry execute skid register for safe younger instructions while EX/MEM is holding an older stalled memory operation. When dmem_stall is asserted and ID/EX holds a valid non-memory, non-branch, non-jump instruction that does not depend on the stalled load's rd, EX computes it once and captures the full ex_mem_t result into the skid entry. The front end and ID/EX then remain held until the older memory operation completes; after the memory instruction retires, the skid entry drains into the normal EX/MEM to MEM/WB path before any newly decoded instruction advances.\n8: \n9:   This is intentionally not a general store buffer, fetch FIFO, or out-of-order engine. It only hides one cycle of memory backpressure for independent straight-line ALU/LUI/AUIPC/MUL-class work, preserves strict in-order RVFI retirement by draining after the older memory op, and leaves loads, stores, branches, jumps, and load-dependent consumers on the existing conservative path. CoreMark has many pointer and loop instructions interleaved with memory traffic, so recovering even one cycle from a fraction of randomized dmem stalls should improve iterations/cycle with less hot-path cost than prior structural buffering attempts.\n10: expected_impact:\n11:   fitness_delta_pct: 4\n12:   confidence: medium\n13: changes:\n14:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n15:     description: \"Reuse ex_mem_t as the skid payload and, if needed, add a small packed control record for skid valid/blocked state without changing top-level IO.\"\n16:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n17:     description: \"Expose a skiddable EX result path for valid non-memory, non-control instructions during an EX/MEM dmem hold, while keeping normal EX/MEM behavior unchanged when no skid is taken.\"\n18:   - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n19:     description: \"Add control for capture-on-dmem-stall, skid-full backpressure, and skid-drain priority so the captured instruction is not duplicated and IF/ID remains ordered.\"\n20:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n21:     description: \"Wire the skid valid/payload between EX, hazard control, and MEM so the older memory operation retires first and the skidded instruction drains through channel 0 afterward.\"\n\n(End of file - total 21 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-002-r11s1\ntitle: \"Skid one ALU op behind dmem stalls\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The current pipeline freezes every stage whenever a load or store in MEM waits for io_dmemReady. Prior structural attempts that added front-end queues or a store buffer regressed because they added broad control and memory-ordering muxes, but randomized dmem backpressure is still a direct IPC limiter. A narrower structural change can use the first blocked cycle behind a memory operation without changing prediction, memory ordering, or the NRET=1 RVFI contract.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a one-entry execute skid register for safe younger instructions while EX/MEM is holding an older stalled memory operation. When dmem_stall is asserted and ID/EX holds a valid non-memory, non-branch, non-jump instruction that does not depend on the stalled load's rd, EX computes it once and captures the full ex_mem_t result into the skid entry. The front end and ID/EX then remain held until the older memory operation completes; after the memory instruction retires, the skid entry drains into the normal EX/MEM to MEM/WB path before any newly decoded instruction advances.\n\n  This is intentionally not a general store buffer, fetch FIFO, or out-of-order engine. It only hides one cycle of memory backpressure for independent straight-line ALU/LUI/AUIPC/MUL-class work, preserves strict in-order RVFI retirement by draining after the older memory op, and leaves loads, stores, branches, jumps, and load-dependent consumers on the existing conservative path. CoreMark has many pointer and loop instructions interleaved with memory traffic, so recovering even one cycle from a fraction of randomized dmem stalls should improve iterations/cycle with less hot-path cost than prior structural buffering attempts.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Reuse ex_mem_t as the skid payload and, if needed, add a small packed control record for skid valid/blocked state without changing top-level IO.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Expose a skiddable EX result path for valid non-memory, non-control instructions during an EX/MEM dmem hold, while keeping normal EX/MEM behavior unchanged when no skid is taken.\"\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: \"Add control for capture-on-dmem-stall, skid-full backpressure, and skid-drain priority so the captured instruction is not duplicated and IF/ID remains ordered.\"\n  - file: rtl/core.sv","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778631502375,"end":1778631502455}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03a990bfa4cc7b05016a03c34e3f40819b8386386cdb1a7baa"}},"id":"prt_e1eb2ea140019XOp7TDZ5rRdQ2","sessionID":"ses_1e14ed357ffeA57MiySdQujFwm","messageID":"msg_e1eb2cda9001yqpm39ueZ2F0XA"}}
