{"type":"text","timestamp":1778632378257,"sessionID":"ses_1e14018a1ffeD2SrJ9GK5q1FrR","part":{"id":"prt_e1ec04467001zLz8ECB4T238bo","messageID":"msg_e1ec009b4001igD6n4GEoZxFAr","sessionID":"ses_1e14018a1ffeD2SrJ9GK5q1FrR","type":"text","text":"Prior structural attempts show broad decoupling, store buffering, IF registration, early JALR, divider sidecars, and one-entry skid execution all regressed. The remaining plausible structural target is narrower: remove unnecessary global pipeline freezing on instruction-fetch stalls without adding a queue or changing redirect prediction.","time":{"start":1778632377447,"end":1778632378255},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_01574a4429d4e1e9016a03c6b95bc081999fc294b8347076f1","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778632403975,"sessionID":"ses_1e14018a1ffeD2SrJ9GK5q1FrR","part":{"id":"prt_e1ec0a9ed001UJYec4PNwFHLi0","messageID":"msg_e1ec009b4001igD6n4GEoZxFAr","sessionID":"ses_1e14018a1ffeD2SrJ9GK5q1FrR","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a focused structural hypothesis that retimes the writeback-value selection into the MEM/WB register, avoiding new buffering or predictor state while reducing WB forwarding fanout.","time":{"start":1778632403437,"end":1778632403974},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_01574a4429d4e1e9016a03c6d32eb481998be9ce136659b8e9","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778632414822,"sessionID":"ses_1e14018a1ffeD2SrJ9GK5q1FrR","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_6q6eVJJEqF3IWovURe1b5Umb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r12s1\n+title: \"Register final writeback value\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current MEM/WB stage carries both alu_result and read_data, then selects the\n+  architectural writeback value through a combinational WB mux. That mux output\n+  fans out to the register file write port, same-cycle regfile read bypass,\n+  MEM/WB-to-EX forwarding, and RVFI rd_wdata. Prior structural attempts that\n+  added queues, buffers, or sidecars regressed because they added broad control;\n+  this targets a narrower pipeline-boundary fanout point without changing IPC.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a preselected rd_wdata field to the MEM/WB payload and compute it in\n+  mem_stage when the MEM/WB register captures. Loads register the extended\n+  load_data, while ALU/JAL/JALR/LUI/AUIPC results register the existing\n+  alu_result. Then make wb_stage and RVFI consume that registered final value\n+  directly instead of rebuilding the mem_to_reg mux in WB. This should shorten\n+  the WB forwarding and register-file bypass cone, reduce ctrl.mem_to_reg\n+  fanout, and preserve the current single-retire RVFI ordering and all memory\n+  metadata. During dmem stalls, the held MEM/WB fields keep the registered\n+  rd_wdata alive for the existing forwarding behavior while valid is cleared.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add an rd_wdata field to mem_wb_t so the final architectural writeback value is registered at the MEM/WB boundary.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Populate mem_wb_t.rd_wdata with load_data for loads and alu_result for non-load register writes, preserving held fields during dmem stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the combinational mem_to_reg writeback mux with a direct registered rd_wdata output.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Drive RVFI rd_wdata and MEM/WB forwarding from the registered writeback value while keeping the NRET=1 top-level port set unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r12s1\n+title: \"Register final writeback value\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current MEM/WB stage carries both alu_result and read_data, then selects the\n+  architectural writeback value through a combinational WB mux. That mux output\n+  fans out to the register file write port, same-cycle regfile read bypass,\n+  MEM/WB-to-EX forwarding, and RVFI rd_wdata. Prior structural attempts that\n+  added queues, buffers, or sidecars regressed because they added broad control;\n+  this targets a narrower pipeline-boundary fanout point without changing IPC.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a preselected rd_wdata field to the MEM/WB payload and compute it in\n+  mem_stage when the MEM/WB register captures. Loads register the extended\n+  load_data, while ALU/JAL/JALR/LUI/AUIPC results register the existing\n+  alu_result. Then make wb_stage and RVFI consume that registered final value\n+  directly instead of rebuilding the mem_to_reg mux in WB. This should shorten\n+  the WB forwarding and register-file bypass cone, reduce ctrl.mem_to_reg\n+  fanout, and preserve the current single-retire RVFI ordering and all memory\n+  metadata. During dmem stalls, the held MEM/WB fields keep the registered\n+  rd_wdata alive for the existing forwarding behavior while valid is cleared.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add an rd_wdata field to mem_wb_t so the final architectural writeback value is registered at the MEM/WB boundary.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Populate mem_wb_t.rd_wdata with load_data for loads and alu_result for non-load register writes, preserving held fields during dmem stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the combinational mem_to_reg writeback mux with a direct registered rd_wdata output.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Drive RVFI rd_wdata and MEM/WB forwarding from the registered writeback value while keeping the NRET=1 top-level port set unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r12