{"type":"text","timestamp":1778633228009,"sessionID":"ses_1e1339b1cffesslSmGak1zCNhN","part":{"id":"prt_e1ecd3ab00019NlQmaWsxeKrdM","messageID":"msg_e1ecc88ec001E7SHYrIf6nhgig","sessionID":"ses_1e1339b1cffesslSmGak1zCNhN","type":"text","text":"The structural history points away from queues, buffers, early JALR, divider sidecars, and broad stall decoupling. I’ll write a narrower structural retiming hypothesis: precompute forwarding selections before EX so the critical EX operand-select path loses the rd/rs comparator cone that recently proved timing-sensitive.","time":{"start":1778633226928,"end":1778633228007},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0f8b407cbdacc177016a03ca0aabf081998701d0f00d91f3f3","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778633239511,"sessionID":"ses_1e1339b1cffesslSmGak1zCNhN","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_WU4LhEmiUfnh8DxwuSqAChB7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r13s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r13s1\n+title: \"Predecode forwarding selects\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The most recent improvement came from factoring duplicated forwarding matches, which strongly suggests the EX operand-select path is still timing-sensitive. Prior structural attempts with FIFOs, store buffers, divider sidecars, and dmem skid slots regressed because they added broad control to common paths. A narrower structural retiming can target the same hot forwarding cone without changing CoreMark IPC or memory ordering.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move the producer/consumer rd-vs-rs comparisons for EX forwarding one stage earlier and carry predecoded rs1/rs2 forwarding selects in the ID/EX payload. In ID, compare the decoded instruction's source fields against the current ID/EX producer that will become EX/MEM and the current EX/MEM producer that will become MEM/WB, then latch compact select hints alongside the operands. EX keeps only the small operand muxes and the existing ready-qualified MEM-load handling, with a fallback or hold behavior that preserves correctness through dmem stalls and redirects.\n+\n+  This should shorten the common EX path from comparator-plus-priority-plus-mux to mostly muxing, building on the proven forwarding-match optimization while avoiding new queues, predictor state, or out-of-order retirement risk. RVFI source values remain the post-forward operands latched into EX/MEM, and the NRET=1 retirement contract is unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact rs1/rs2 forwarding-select fields to id_ex_t so forwarding decisions can be carried into EX with the instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch predecoded forwarding hints from top-level producer metadata alongside the existing ID/EX operands and control bundle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire current ID/EX and EX/MEM producer metadata into the predecode logic and pass latched forwarding selects to EX, preserving stall and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Refactor the forwarding unit to compute next-cycle select hints from IF/ID source fields and current producer stages rather than comparing in the EX cycle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consume the latched forwarding selects directly for operand muxing while retaining MEM-load ready qualification for branches and JALR redirects.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r13s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r13s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r13s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r13s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r13s1\n+title: \"Predecode forwarding selects\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The most recent improvement came from factoring duplicated forwarding matches, which strongly suggests the EX operand-select path is still timing-sensitive. Prior structural attempts with FIFOs, store buffers, divider sidecars, and dmem skid slots regressed because they added broad control to common paths. A narrower structural retiming can target the same hot forwarding cone without changing CoreMark IPC or memory ordering.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move the producer/consumer rd-vs-rs comparisons for EX forwarding one stage earlier and carry predecoded rs1/rs2 forwarding selects in the ID/EX payload. In ID, compare the decoded instruction's source fields against the current ID/EX producer that will become EX/MEM and the current EX/MEM producer that will become MEM/WB, then latch compact select hints alongside the operands. EX keeps only the small operand muxes and the existing ready-qualified MEM-load handling, with a fallback or hold behavior that preserves correctness through dmem stalls and redirects.\n+\n+  This should shorten the common EX path from comparator-plus-priority-plus-mux to mostly muxing, building on the proven forwarding-match optimization while avoiding new queues, predictor state, or out-of-order retirement risk. RVFI source values remain the post-forward operands latched into EX/MEM, and the NRET=1 retirement contract is unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact rs1/rs2 forwarding-select fields to id_ex_t so forwarding decisions can be carried into EX with the instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch predecoded forwarding hints from top-level producer metadata alongside the existing ID/EX operands and control bundle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire current ID/EX and EX/MEM producer metadata into the predecode logic and pass latched forwarding selects to EX, preserving stall and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Refactor the forwarding unit to compute next-cycle select hints from IF/ID source fields and current producer stages rather than comparing in the EX cycle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consume the latched forwarding selects directly for operand muxing while retaining MEM-load ready qualification for branches and JALR redirects.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r13s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r13s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r13s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r13s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r13s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r13s1\n+title: \"Predecode forwarding selects\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The most recent improvement came from factoring duplicated forwarding matches, which strongly suggests the EX operand-select path is still timing-sensitive. Prior structural attempts with FIFOs, store buffers, divider sidecars, and dmem skid slots regressed because they added broad control to common paths. A narrower structural retiming can target the same hot forwarding cone without changing CoreMark IPC or memory ordering.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move the producer/consumer rd-vs-rs comparisons for EX forwarding one stage earlier and carry predecoded rs1/rs2 forwarding selects in the ID/EX payload. In ID, compare the decoded instruction's source fields against the current ID/EX producer that will become EX/MEM and the current EX/MEM producer that will become MEM/WB, then latch compact select hints alongside the operands. EX keeps only the small operand muxes and the existing ready-qualified MEM-load handling, with a fallback or hold behavior that preserves correctness through dmem stalls and redirects.\n+\n+  This should shorten the common EX path from comparator-plus-priority-plus-mux to mostly muxing, building on the proven forwarding-match optimization while avoiding new queues, predictor state, or out-of-order retirement risk. RVFI source values remain the post-forward operands latched into EX/MEM, and the NRET=1 retirement contract is unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact rs1/rs2 forwarding-select fields to id_ex_t so forwarding decisions can be carried into EX with the instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch predecoded forwarding hints from top-level producer metadata alongside the existing ID/EX operands and control bundle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire current ID/EX and EX/MEM producer metadata into the predecode logic and pass latched forwarding selects to EX, preserving stall and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Refactor the forwarding unit to compute next-cycle select hints from IF/ID source fields and current producer stages rather than comparing in the EX cycle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consume the latched forwarding selects directly for operand muxing while retaining MEM-load ready qualification for branches and JALR redirects.\"\n","additions":23,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r13s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778633239508,"end":1778633239511}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f8b407cbdacc177016a03ca0bee0081999fb09b19dbe934a0"}},"id":"prt_e1ecd3ee9001ssVRIzvF1E8E95","sessionID":"ses_1e1339b1cffesslSmGak1zCNhN","messageID":"msg_e1ecc88ec001E7SHYrIf6nhgig"}}
