{"type":"text","timestamp":1778634207514,"sessionID":"ses_1e1249795ffeRbMy3U6KW9KAfw","part":{"id":"prt_e1edc3073001c8TqS4sCkWrVTV","messageID":"msg_e1edb90af001pdXtdKcLRgfPXS","sessionID":"ses_1e1249795ffeRbMy3U6KW9KAfw","type":"text","text":"The relevant structural history shows broad queues, store buffering, IF/ID registration, divider sidecars, EX skid slots, and forwarding predecode all regressed; the one durable structural win was a targeted pipeline-boundary bypass. I’m going to write a narrow structural hypothesis that moves memory lane/request metadata across an existing pipeline boundary without adding queues, predictors, or new retirement behavior.","time":{"start":1778634207347,"end":1778634207511},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_095f9d799663b6a4016a03cddf16d08199b5410d7fdad0ef9a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
