{"type":"text","timestamp":1778635229895,"sessionID":"ses_1e1157fe9ffeEQjSjtaf5Jv3G5","part":{"id":"prt_e1eebca75001ahsKjZwu1SV0qc","messageID":"msg_e1eead4e2001xhxGWp493rffVa","sessionID":"ses_1e1157fe9ffeEQjSjtaf5Jv3G5","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a narrow structural retiming hypothesis that targets the regfile read/writeback boundary without adding queues, predictors, sidecars, or memory-ordering state.","time":{"start":1778635229813,"end":1778635229895},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0b0116fe8f9cce42016a03d1ddb08c819ab8f1119644acda44","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778635234780,"sessionID":"ses_1e1157fe9ffeEQjSjtaf5Jv3G5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ElSrQaZ7ypFny2PYGdbDv3CG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Retimed WB-to-ID register bypass\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core keeps write-first bypass muxes inside the integer register file.\n+  That makes the WB-stage write data and destination comparators part of both\n+  combinational read ports, even though the only architectural need is that the\n+  value captured into ID/EX reflects same-cycle writeback. Prior register-file\n+  storage rewrites regressed because they changed the physical array and reset\n+  behavior; this is a narrower structural retiming of the bypass boundary.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Make reg_file a simpler x0-guarded asynchronous read plus synchronous write\n+  array, and move the same-cycle WB bypass into id_stage at the point where\n+  rs1_val and rs2_val are captured into the ID/EX register. Core wires the WB\n+  enable, address, and final writeback data into ID so decode can select the\n+  just-written value only for the two source operands entering the pipeline.\n+\n+  This preserves the existing architectural behavior, EX forwarding priority,\n+  RVFI source-value reporting, and NRET=1 retirement contract, but removes the\n+  high-fanout writeback mux/data path from the regfile read module and may give\n+  synthesis a cleaner ID-stage boundary. It should improve Fmax slightly with no\n+  CoreMark cycle-count cost and much less risk than another queue, store buffer,\n+  early redirect, or divider sidecar.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/reg_file.sv\n+    description: \"Remove internal same-cycle write-first read bypass muxes while keeping x0 hardwired, synchronous writes, and reset behavior unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add explicit WB bypass inputs and select bypassed rs1_val/rs2_val when the instruction source matches the same-cycle writeback destination.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire wb_w_en, wb_w_addr, and wb_w_data into id_stage so the core-level behavior and RVFI source metadata remain unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Retimed WB-to-ID register bypass\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core keeps write-first bypass muxes inside the integer register file.\n+  That makes the WB-stage write data and destination comparators part of both\n+  combinational read ports, even though the only architectural need is that the\n+  value captured into ID/EX reflects same-cycle writeback. Prior register-file\n+  storage rewrites regressed because they changed the physical array and reset\n+  behavior; this is a narrower structural retiming of the bypass boundary.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Make reg_file a simpler x0-guarded asynchronous read plus synchronous write\n+  array, and move the same-cycle WB bypass into id_stage at the point where\n+  rs1_val and rs2_val are captured into the ID/EX register. Core wires the WB\n+  enable, address, and final writeback data into ID so decode can select the\n+  just-written value only for the two source operands entering the pipeline.\n+\n+  This preserves the existing architectural behavior, EX forwarding priority,\n+  RVFI source-value reporting, and NRET=1 retirement contract, but removes the\n+  high-fanout writeback mux/data path from the regfile read module and may give\n+  synthesis a cleaner ID-stage boundary. It should improve Fmax slightly with no\n+  CoreMark cycle-count cost and much less risk than another queue, store buffer,\n+  early redirect, or divider sidecar.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/reg_file.sv\n+    description: \"Remove internal same-cycle write-first read bypass muxes while keeping x0 hardwired, synchronous writes, and reset behavior unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add explicit WB bypass inputs and select bypassed rs1_val/rs2_val when the instruction source matches the same-cycle writeback destination.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire wb_w_en, wb_w_addr, and wb_w_data into id_stage so the core-level behavior and RVFI source metadata remain unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+