{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778621371430,"sessionID":"ses_1e1e8be8effe4chNq5q8IM7F5D","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_nWKar78RMxHak2YoeeiNWkVP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r2s1\n+title: \"Add one-entry store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  CoreMark is evaluated with randomized dmem backpressure, and the current pipeline\n+  freezes all stages whenever a store in MEM sees io_dmemReady=0. Stores do not\n+  produce a register result, so blocking fetch, decode, and execute behind every\n+  delayed store wastes cycles that could otherwise retire independent ALU and\n+  control-flow work. The prior structural fetch FIFO did not help enough because\n+  it buffered only fall-through front-end work; this targets the back-end stall\n+  source directly.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry store buffer between MEM and the external dmem write port.\n+  A non-MMIO store can retire into the buffer when the bus is not ready, allowing\n+  younger non-memory instructions to continue while the buffer drains in the\n+  background. Loads and subsequent stores should stall while the buffer is valid\n+  unless the implementation adds exact same-address forwarding; MMIO marker and\n+  UART stores should keep the existing blocking behavior so CoreMark timing and\n+  output ordering remain exact. This should recover cycles from randomized store\n+  stalls with modest control and register cost, while preserving single-channel\n+  RVFI order by retiring each store only after it is captured in the ordered\n+  buffer.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add any store-buffer metadata needed to distinguish buffered stores from loads and preserve RVFI memory fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire a one-entry store buffer between mem_stage and the dmem write interface without changing the NRET=1 top-level ports.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Allow ordinary stores to retire into the buffer on dmem backpressure while keeping loads and MMIO stores blocking and RVFI-accurate.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the blanket store dmem stall with buffer-full, load, MMIO, and memory-ordering stalls so independent younger work can proceed.\"\n+  - file: rtl/store_buffer.sv\n+    description: \"Add a small ordered store buffer that holds address, data, mask, valid, and MMIO/blocking policy while driving dmem until ready.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r2s1\n+title: \"Add one-entry store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  CoreMark is evaluated with randomized dmem backpressure, and the current pipeline\n+  freezes all stages whenever a store in MEM sees io_dmemReady=0. Stores do not\n+  produce a register result, so blocking fetch, decode, and execute behind every\n+  delayed store wastes cycles that could otherwise retire independent ALU and\n+  control-flow work. The prior structural fetch FIFO did not help enough because\n+  it buffered only fall-through front-end work; this targets the back-end stall\n+  source directly.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry store buffer between MEM and the external dmem write port.\n+  A non-MMIO store can retire into the buffer when the bus is not ready, allowing\n+  younger non-memory instructions to continue while the buffer drains in the\n+  background. Loads and subsequent stores should stall while the buffer is valid\n+  unless the implementation adds exact same-address forwarding; MMIO marker and\n+  UART stores should keep the existing blocking behavior so CoreMark timing and\n+  output ordering remain exact. This should recover cycles from randomized store\n+  stalls with modest control and register cost, while preserving single-channel\n+  RVFI order by retiring each store only after it is captured in the ordered\n+  buffer.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add any store-buffer metadata needed to distinguish buffered stores from loads and preserve RVFI memory fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire a one-entry store buffer between mem_stage and the dmem write interface without changing the NRET=1 top-level ports.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Allow ordinary stores to retire into the buffer on dmem backpressure while keeping loads and MMIO stores blocking and RVFI-accurate.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the blanket store dmem stall with buffer-full, load, MMIO, and memory-ordering stalls so independent younger work can proceed.\"\n+  - file: rtl/store_buffer.sv\n+    description: \"Add a small ordered store buffer that holds address, data, mask, valid, and MMIO/blocking policy while driving dmem until ready.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/exper