{"type":"text","timestamp":1778622416706,"sessionID":"ses_1e1d8d25dffey9i65XgibXjQC0","part":{"id":"prt_e1e283bd4001nTE2SxpNYer3fD","messageID":"msg_e1e274b87001kV1HQXylNXGv0B","sessionID":"ses_1e1d8d25dffey9i65XgibXjQC0","type":"text","text":"Prior structural attempts tried front-end decoupling and a store buffer; both added state/control without enough CoreMark payoff. The more promising structural angle is a targeted MEM-to-EX load-result bypass that removes true load-use bubbles while preserving the existing single-retire pipeline and avoiding broad front-end changes.","time":{"start":1778622413780,"end":1778622416704},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07270d26ae6398ae016a039fcda94881909239557916e4e4f9","phase":"commentary"}}}}
