{"type":"text","timestamp":1778622423415,"sessionID":"ses_1e1d8d25dffey9i65XgibXjQC0","part":{"id":"prt_e1e285f50001qy34KCiyAn13nG","messageID":"msg_e1e2847d6001z6cMuhzjm2hyLZ","sessionID":"ses_1e1d8d25dffey9i65XgibXjQC0","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis YAML now with the required ID, structural category, and short `rtl/...` change paths only.","time":{"start":1778622422864,"end":1778622423413},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0f20ba85fd0229fd016a039fd6c3f08195b638d69f9314ace2","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778622435529,"sessionID":"ses_1e1d8d25dffey9i65XgibXjQC0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_cPFpDM5ZGp1KaMBljjiuULGz","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r3s1\n+title: \"Add MEM-to-EX load forwarding\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage pipeline still pays a full interlock bubble whenever an\n+  instruction immediately consumes a preceding load. CoreMark's pointer-heavy list,\n+  matrix, and state kernels create many load-use pairs, and the existing zero-wait\n+  memory model makes the loaded word available in MEM soon enough to be forwarded\n+  into the dependent instruction's EX operand path. Prior structural attempts added\n+  queues or buffers with broad control cost; this targets a specific pipeline\n+  boundary that directly removes retirement bubbles.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a MEM-stage load-result forwarding path into EX and make the forwarding unit\n+  treat an EX/MEM load as a valid producer once dmem data is ready. The EX-stage\n+  operand muxes should use the sign/zero-extended load data for rs1 and rs2, and\n+  the post-forward operand values must continue to be latched into EX/MEM so RVFI\n+  rs1/rs2 metadata matches the architectural source values. With that bypass in\n+  place, the load-use interlock can stop stalling ordinary dependent ALU, branch,\n+  address, and store-data consumers; dmem stalls still freeze the pipeline until\n+  the forwarded load result is valid, and redirect generation must not use an\n+  unready forwarded load operand. This should improve CoreMark IPC without adding\n+  predictor state, store ordering machinery, or changing the NRET=1 RVFI contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose the MEM-stage writeback-equivalent load result as a combinational forwarding value, including the existing byte/halfword sign-extension logic.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a forwarding selection for EX/MEM loads so dependent rs1 and rs2 operands can source the MEM-stage load result instead of forcing a bubble.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a MEM-load forwarding input and operand mux case, latch the forwarded values into RVFI source metadata, and suppress redirects while a forwarded load operand is not ready.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the blanket one-cycle load-use interlock when the MEM-to-EX bypass can satisfy the dependency, while preserving full-pipeline holds on real dmem stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the MEM-stage load-forwarding data and readiness into EX and the forwarding/hazard logic without changing the top-level IO shape.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r3s1\n+title: \"Add MEM-to-EX load forwarding\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage pipeline still pays a full interlock bubble whenever an\n+  instruction immediately consumes a preceding load. CoreMark's pointer-heavy list,\n+  matrix, and state kernels create many load-use pairs, and the existing zero-wait\n+  memory model makes the loaded word available in MEM soon enough to be forwarded\n+  into the dependent instruction's EX operand path. Prior structural attempts added\n+  queues or buffers with broad control cost; this targets a specific pipeline\n+  boundary that directly removes retirement bubbles.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a MEM-stage load-result forwarding path into EX and make the forwarding unit\n+  treat an EX/MEM load as a valid producer once dmem data is ready. The EX-stage\n+  operand muxes should use the sign/zero-extended load data for rs1 and rs2, and\n+  the post-forward operand values must continue to be latched into EX/MEM so RVFI\n+  rs1/rs2 metadata matches the architectural source values. With that bypass in\n+  place, the load-use interlock can stop stalling ordinary dependent ALU, branch,\n+  address, and store-data consumers; dmem stalls still freeze the pipeline until\n+  the forwarded load result is valid, and redirect generation must not use an\n+  unready forwarded load operand. This should improve CoreMark IPC without adding\n+  predictor state, store ordering machinery, or changing the NRET=1 RVFI contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose the MEM-stage writeback-equivalent load result as a combinational forwarding value, including the existing byte/halfword sign-extension logic.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a forwarding selection for EX/MEM loads so dependent rs1 and rs2 operands can source the MEM-stage load result instead of forcing a bubble.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a MEM-load forwarding input and operand mux case, latch the forwarded values into RVFI source metadata, and suppress redirects while a forwarded load operand is not ready.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the blanket one-cycle load-use interlock when the MEM-to-EX bypass can satisfy the dependency, while preserving full-pipeline holds on real dmem stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the MEM-stage load-forwarding data and readiness into EX and the forwarding/hazard logic without changing the top-level IO shape.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r3s1\n+title: \"Add MEM-to-EX load forwarding\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage pipeline still pays a full interlock bubble whenever an\n+  instruction immediately consumes a preceding load. CoreMark's pointer-heavy list,\n+  matrix, and state kernels create many load-use pairs, and the existing zero-wait\n+  memory model makes the loaded word available in MEM soon enough to be forwarded\n+  into the dependent instruction's EX operand path. Prior structural attempts added\n+  queues or buffers with broad control cost; this targets a specific pipeline\n+  boundary that directly removes retirement bubbles.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a MEM-stage load-result forwarding path into EX and make the forwarding unit\n+  treat an EX/MEM load as a valid producer once dmem data is ready. The EX-stage\n+  operand muxes should use the sign/zero-extended load data for rs1 and rs2, and\n+  the post-forward operand values must continue to be latched into EX/MEM so RVFI\n+  rs1/rs2 metadata matches the architectural source values. With that bypass in\n+  place, the load-use interlock can stop stalling ordinary dependent ALU, branch,\n+  address, and store-data consumers; dmem stalls still freeze the pipeline until\n+  the forwarded load result is valid, and redirect generation must not use an\n+  unready forwarded load operand. This should improve CoreMark IPC without adding\n+  predictor state, store ordering machinery, or changing the NRET=1 RVFI contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose the MEM-stage writeback-equivalent load result as a combinational forwarding value, including the existing byte/halfword sign-extension logic.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a forwarding selection for EX/MEM loads so dependent rs1 and rs2 operands can source the MEM-stage load result instead of forcing a bubble.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a MEM-load forwarding input and operand mux case, latch the forwarded values into RVFI source metadata, and suppress redirects while a forwarded load operand is not ready.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the blanket one-cycle load-use interlock when the MEM-to-EX bypass can satisfy the dependency, while preserving full-pipeline holds on real dmem stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the MEM-stage load-forwarding data and readiness into EX and the forwarding/hazard logic without changing the top-level IO shape.\"\n","additions":36,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778622435519,"end":1778622435527}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f20ba85fd0229fd016a039fd753308195b50a8bf8ad0d241e"}},"id":"pr