{"type":"text","timestamp":1778623856508,"sessionID":"ses_1e1c2c67fffeQCY3WV3IzmhDq6","part":{"id":"prt_e1e3e3cde001n7SUqp5drC1dMf","messageID":"msg_e1e3d82ab0026Kd2cPi2vkiMMm","sessionID":"ses_1e1c2c67fffeQCY3WV3IzmhDq6","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a structural RV32M divide/remodel proposal, because the current combinational `/` and `%` operators likely dominate FPGA timing and LUT cost while CoreMark’s bracketed hot loop should rarely pay DIV/REM latency.","time":{"start":1778623855838,"end":1778623856508},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0272f6b2ce106a56016a03a56fb7188199a793c0d25ce45eac","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778623865567,"sessionID":"ses_1e1c2c67fffeQCY3WV3IzmhDq6","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_W0TqM3ZJZ9fb2sBOaV1Oc0Gj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r4s1\n+title: Move DIV/REM off EX critical path\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX-stage ALU contains fully combinational RV32M division and\n+  remainder operators. Even when CoreMark rarely executes DIV/REM inside the\n+  timed region, synthesis must still route those large operators through the\n+  ALU result mux, which is a plausible Fmax and LUT bottleneck on the Tang Nano\n+  20K. Prior structural wins came from targeted pipeline-boundary changes, not\n+  broad queues or buffering, so the best next structural angle is to remove a\n+  rare long-latency operator from the common one-cycle EX path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU datapath with a small iterative\n+  RV32M divide unit that stalls EX only while an actual divide or remainder is\n+  in flight. Keep ADD/SUB/logic/shift/branch address/MUL operations on the\n+  existing single-cycle path, and preserve the RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitution\n+  as a one-cycle formal-only path. This should raise median FPGA Fmax and reduce\n+  LUT pressure with little CoreMark IPC cost, while exact RV32M results remain\n+  covered by the existing ALU/cosim tests and formal-deep.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real DIV/REM/% operators from the common combinational ALU path while keeping non-DIV operations and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior one-cycle exact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate/control an iterative divide-remainder unit, hold the EX/MEM register while it runs, and latch the completed result into the normal ALU result field.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX busy stall input so IF/ID/EX hold cleanly during a real DIV/REM without double retirement or dropping redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the EX busy stall into the existing pipeline control without changing the nret=1 top-level IO or RVFI channel contract.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend RV32M divide/remainder coverage, including divide-by-zero and INT_MIN/-1 cases, to guard the new iterative unit.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r4s1\n+title: Move DIV/REM off EX critical path\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX-stage ALU contains fully combinational RV32M division and\n+  remainder operators. Even when CoreMark rarely executes DIV/REM inside the\n+  timed region, synthesis must still route those large operators through the\n+  ALU result mux, which is a plausible Fmax and LUT bottleneck on the Tang Nano\n+  20K. Prior structural wins came from targeted pipeline-boundary changes, not\n+  broad queues or buffering, so the best next structural angle is to remove a\n+  rare long-latency operator from the common one-cycle EX path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU datapath with a small iterative\n+  RV32M divide unit that stalls EX only while an actual divide or remainder is\n+  in flight. Keep ADD/SUB/logic/shift/branch address/MUL operations on the\n+  existing single-cycle path, and preserve the RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitution\n+  as a one-cycle formal-only path. This should raise median FPGA Fmax and reduce\n+  LUT pressure with little CoreMark IPC cost, while exact RV32M results remain\n+  covered by the existing ALU/cosim tests and formal-deep.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real DIV/REM/% operators from the common combinational ALU path while keeping non-DIV operations and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior one-cycle exact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate/control an iterative divide-remainder unit, hold the EX/MEM register while it runs, and latch the completed result into the normal ALU result field.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX busy stall input so IF/ID/EX hold cleanly during a real DIV/REM without double retirement or dropping redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the EX busy stall into the existing pipeline control without changing the nret=1 top-level IO or RVFI channel contract.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend RV32M divide/remainder coverage, including divide-by-zero and INT_MIN/-1 cases, to guard the new iterative unit.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.clau