{"type":"text","timestamp":1778629387115,"sessionID":"ses_1e16dcdc2ffeBnZsTvhJ8lSuav","part":{"id":"prt_e1e929f99001NWKyhEiSTKiqvi","messageID":"msg_e1e92555f001ukFFqXIIJvHqa7","sessionID":"ses_1e16dcdc2ffeBnZsTvhJ8lSuav","type":"text","text":"The structural history shows broad buffering and store decoupling regressed, while the one targeted pipeline-boundary change that paid was MEM-to-EX load forwarding. I’m going to keep the new hypothesis similarly narrow and avoid adding IF predictor state or bus queues.","time":{"start":1778629386137,"end":1778629387111},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_016ec847f39a0a01016a03bb0a0c7081959159b9bdd66f5e7c","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778629388284,"sessionID":"ses_1e16dcdc2ffeBnZsTvhJ8lSuav","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_lel5ahpHXMDChatj81QJwsC6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","offset":12,"limit":1},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n12: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260512-002-r4s1\", \"title\": \"Move DIV/REM off EX critical path\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current EX-stage ALU contains fully combinational RV32M division and\\nremainder operators. Even when CoreMark rarely executes DIV/REM inside the\\ntimed region, synthesis must still route those large operators through the\\nALU result mux, which is a plausible Fmax and LUT bottleneck on the Tang Nano\\n20K. Prior structural wins came from targeted pipeline-boundary changes, not\\nbroad queues or buffering, so the best next structural angle is to remove a\\nrare long-latency operator from the common one-cycle EX path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current EX-stage ALU contains fully combinational RV32M division and\\nremainder operators. Even when CoreMark rarely executes DIV/REM inside the\\ntimed region, synthesis must still route those large operators through the\\nALU result mux, which is a plausible Fmax and LUT bottleneck on the Tang Nano\\n20K. Prior structural wins came from targeted pipeline-boundary changes, not\\nbroad queues or buffering, so the best next structural angle is to remove a\\nrare long-latency operator from the common one-cycle EX path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Replace the combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU datapath with a small iterative\\nRV32M divide unit that stalls EX only while an actual divide or remainder is\\nin flight. Keep ADD/SUB/logic/shift/branch address/MUL operations on the\\nexisting single-cycle path, and preserve the RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitution\\nas a one-cycle formal-only path. This should raise median FPGA Fmax and reduce\\nLUT pressure with little CoreMark IPC cost, while exact RV32M results remain\\ncovered by the existing ALU/cosim tests and formal-deep.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 6, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove real DIV/REM/% operators from the common combinational ALU path while keeping non-DIV operations and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n(Showing lines 12-12 of 25. Use offset=13 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260512-002-r4s1\", \"title\": \"Move DIV/REM off EX critical path\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current EX-stage ALU contains fully combinational RV32M division and\\nremainder operators. Even when CoreMark rarely executes DIV/REM inside the\\ntimed region, synthesis must still route those large operators through the\\nALU result mux, which is a plausible Fmax and LUT bottleneck on the Tang Nano\\n20K. Prior structural wins came from targeted pipeline-boundary changes, not\\nbroad queues or buffering, so the best next structural angle is to remove a\\nrare long-latency operator from the common one-cycle EX path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current EX-stage ALU contains fully combinational RV32M division and\\nremainder operators. Even when CoreMark rarely executes DIV/REM inside the\\ntimed region, synthesis must still route those large operators through the\\nALU result mux, which is a plausible Fmax and LUT bottleneck on the Tang Nano\\n20K. Prior structural wins came from targeted pipeline-boundary changes, not\\nbroad queues or buffering, so the best next structural angle is to remove a\\nrare long-latency operator from the common one-cycle EX path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Replace the combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU datapath with a small iterative\\nRV32M divide unit that stalls EX only while an actual divide or remainder is\\nin flight. Keep ADD/SUB/logic/shift/branch address/MUL operations on the\\nexisting single-cycle path, and preserve the RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitution\\nas a one-cycle formal-only path. This should raise median FPGA Fmax and reduce\\nLUT pressure with little CoreMark IPC cost, while exact RV32M results remain\\ncovered by the existing ALU/cosim tests and formal-deep.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 6, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove real DIV/REM/% operators from the common combinational ALU path while keeping non-DIV operations and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","time":{"start":1778629388273,"end":1778629388283}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_016ec847f39a0a01016a03bb0b08f881958c0fb5a074ea607d"}},"id":"prt_e1e92a36b001Pafy0C7pC44sgH","sessionID":"ses_1e16dcdc2ffeBnZsTvhJ8lSuav","messageID":"msg_e1e92555f001ukFFqXIIJvHqa7"}}
