\n24:   This targets median FPGA Fmax with no CoreMark IPC change and avoids the failed\n25:   predictor pattern of adding IF-stage state or new target paths. The change is\n26:   intentionally narrower than the failed EX target-arithmetic gating attempt: it\n27:   does not gate or restructure branch target, jump target, or comparator inputs,\n28:   only the final predictor-repair decision for instructions that cannot redirect.\n29: expected_impact:\n30:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n31:   confidence: medium\n32: changes:\n33:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n34:     description: \"Gate redirect assertion with the resolved instruction's control-flow class before using the pred_next_pc mismatch result, while preserving existing branch/jump target computation and trap behavior.\"\n\n(End of file - total 34 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-003-r11s2\ntitle: Gate predictor repair compare\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The current best predictor is the stateless JAL-taken plus backward-branch-taken\n  rule, and the strongest recent predictor win came from making that same policy\n  cheaper rather than smarter. Prior attempts that added BHT, RAS, JALR memo,\n  loop-exit state, richer static direction, fetch buffering, adder sharing, or\n  JAL target gating all regressed from added front-end or control-path cost.\n\n  One remaining always-active cost of the predictor is in EX: every instruction,\n  including ordinary ALU and memory operations, drives the resolved-next-PC versus\n  pred_next_pc mismatch comparator even though only branches and jumps can ever\n  require predictor repair.\nhypothesis: |\n  Preserve the exact existing fetch prediction policy and pred_next_pc metadata,\n  but gate the EX-stage redirect/mispredict compare with the decoded control-flow\n  class. Non-branch, non-jump instructions should never assert redirect, so they\n  can bypass the 32-bit next-PC mismatch check and simply retire with pc+4 as\n  today. Branches and JAL/JALR continue to compute resolved_next_pc exactly as","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778631470955,"end":1778631470963}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bdbb0cc90461db7016a03c32da7d0819bb690c8913d996390"}},"id":"prt_e1eb26ac3001oJ5rdhSZTQHhJA","sessionID":"ses_1e14ed2a4ffehDZT9w0UI0ynQN","messageID":"msg_e1eb25879001txRjufLVcxI5bl"}}
