{"type":"text","timestamp":1778633205445,"sessionID":"ses_1e1339aa6ffe5nCQdLsAolcZhT","part":{"id":"prt_e1ecce383001vdYk3RDFGy8gPq","messageID":"msg_e1ecc8aea001G8GFsMh4CWRw4f","sessionID":"ses_1e1339aa6ffe5nCQdLsAolcZhT","type":"text","text":"The prior predictor data strongly favors preserving the current JAL/backward-branch policy and only reducing fetch-path cost. I’m writing a narrow hypothesis around restructuring `if_stage.sv` predictor selection without adding state, tables, or new redirects.","time":{"start":1778633204611,"end":1778633205445},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_051a9258353d2287016a03c9f47f288199ba5eefbf59c21c9e","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778633212092,"sessionID":"ses_1e1339aa6ffe5nCQdLsAolcZhT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_xIIUzNY0YzoffP9IUfmRbKXC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r13s2\n+title: Prioritize predictor fallthrough path\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only durable predictor win in the bench core is the stateless direct-control policy: predict JAL taken and backward conditional branches taken. Follow-on attempts that added BHT, RAS, JALR memo, loop-exit state, richer static direction, target-adder sharing, JAL gating, or predictor repair gating mostly regressed because extra IF or EX control cost outweighed the remaining saved bubbles.\n+\n+  The current IF predictor still presents a three-way predicted-next-PC mux over pc+4, backward-branch target, and JAL target on every fetch. CoreMark's hot path is dominated by ordinary fall-through instructions plus loop branches, so making fall-through the explicit fast/default predictor path may reduce fetch timing pressure without changing the successful prediction behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/if_stage.sv so the predictor first computes pc_plus4 as the default predicted next PC, then overrides it only for the two existing taken-prediction cases: direct JAL and backward conditional branch. Keep both target adders and the exact same static direction policy, but rewrite the combinational logic as a priority/default assignment rather than a nested ternary select feeding predicted_next_pc.\n+\n+  This is intentionally a predictor implementation cleanup, not a smarter predictor. It adds no tables, tags, counters, RAS, JALR target state, extra carried metadata, or new redirect source. The goal is to help yosys/nextpnr map the overwhelmingly common fall-through path with less mux pressure while preserving IPC, RVFI pc_wdata behavior, redirect repair, and the NRET=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Rewrite static predictor next-PC selection as a pc+4 default with explicit JAL and backward-branch overrides, preserving the existing prediction policy and pred_next_pc metadata.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r13s2\n+title: Prioritize predictor fallthrough path\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only durable predictor win in the bench core is the stateless direct-control policy: predict JAL taken and backward conditional branches taken. Follow-on attempts that added BHT, RAS, JALR memo, loop-exit state, richer static direction, target-adder sharing, JAL gating, or predictor repair gating mostly regressed because extra IF or EX control cost outweighed the remaining saved bubbles.\n+\n+  The current IF predictor still presents a three-way predicted-next-PC mux over pc+4, backward-branch target, and JAL target on every fetch. CoreMark's hot path is dominated by ordinary fall-through instructions plus loop branches, so making fall-through the explicit fast/default predictor path may reduce fetch timing pressure without changing the successful prediction behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/if_stage.sv so the predictor first computes pc_plus4 as the default predicted next PC, then overrides it only for the two existing taken-prediction cases: direct JAL and backward conditional branch. Keep both target adders and the exact same static direction policy, but rewrite the combinational logic as a priority/default assignment rather than a nested ternary select feeding predicted_next_pc.\n+\n+  This is intentionally a predictor implementation cleanup, not a smarter predictor. It adds no tables, tags, counters, RAS, JALR target state, extra carried metadata, or new redirect source. The goal is to help yosys/nextpnr map the overwhelmingly common fall-through path with less mux pressure while preserving IPC, RVFI pc_wdata behavior, redirect repair, and the NRET=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Rewrite static predictor next-PC selection as a pc+4 default with explicit JAL and backward-branch overrides, preserving the existing prediction policy and pred_next_pc metadata.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r13s2\n+title: Prioritize predictor fallthrough path\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only durable predictor win in the bench core is the stateless direct-control policy: predict JAL taken and backward conditional branches taken. Follow-on attempts that added BHT, RAS, JALR memo, loop-exit state, richer static direction, target-adder sharing, JAL gating, or predictor repair gating mostly regressed because extra IF or EX control cost outweighed the remaining saved bubbles.\n+\n+  The current IF predictor still presents a three-way predicted-next-PC mux over pc+4, backward-branch target, and JAL target on every fetch. CoreMark's hot path is dominated by ordinary fall-through instructions plus loop branches, so making fall-through the explicit fast/default predictor path may reduce fetch timing pressure without changing the successful prediction behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/if_stage.sv so the predictor first computes pc_plus4 as the default predicted next PC, then overrides it only for the two existing taken-prediction cases: direct JAL and backward conditional branch. Keep both target adders and the exact same static direction policy, but rewrite the combinational logic as a priority/default assignment rather than a nested ternary select feeding predicted_next_pc.\n+\n+  This is intentionally a predictor implementation cleanup, not a smarter predictor. It adds no tables, tags, counters, RAS, JALR target state, extra carried metadata, or new redirect source. The goal is to help yosys/nextpnr map the overwhelmingly common fall-through path with less mux pressure while preserving IPC, RVFI pc_wdata behavior, redirect repair, and the NRET=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Rewrite static predictor next-PC selection as a pc+4 default with explicit JAL and backward-branch overrides, preserving the existing prediction policy and pred_next_pc metadata.\"\n","additions":17,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncat