{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778634212710,"sessionID":"ses_1e124972effe3tsE3ADLLHjpq9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_u30SqrC1SdrNWOJQTQreViw6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r14s2\n+title: \"Trim predicted PC alignment bits\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor work shows the current stateless JAL-taken plus backward-branch-taken policy is the only durable control-flow win. Attempts to add BHT, RAS, JALR memo, loop-exit learning, richer static direction, target sharing, JAL gating, or fall-through rewrites mostly lost Fmax. The safest remaining predictor angle is therefore to keep the exact policy and reduce only the metadata/control cost around predictor repair.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Carry only pred_next_pc[31:2] through IF/ID and ID/EX, because this RV32IM core has no compressed extension and all architecturally valid fetch PCs are word-aligned. IF still computes the same predicted next PC for its local PC update, while EX reconstructs or compares the aligned high bits when checking resolved_next_pc against the prediction. Misaligned branch or jump targets already trap and use pc+4 as the resolved next PC, so the low two predicted bits are redundant for legal retirement and RVFI pc_wdata remains driven from the resolved next PC.\n+\n+  This preserves the proven prediction behavior and all redirect timing semantics, unlike the failed direction-bit rewrite that forced EX to recompute predictor targets. The expected benefit is small but low-risk: two fewer carried predictor bits in early pipeline payloads and a slightly narrower predictor-repair compare, with no new tables, tags, target muxes, or update state.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Narrow the IF/ID and ID/EX predicted-next-PC metadata to aligned high bits while keeping resolved pc_next/RVFI fields full width.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep the existing static JAL/backward-branch predictor policy, but export only the aligned predicted PC high bits after computing the local next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the narrowed predicted-PC metadata through decode without changing instruction decode, register source metadata, or validity handling.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare the resolved aligned next PC against the carried predicted high bits for redirects while preserving misalignment trap behavior and full-width pc_next reporting.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r14s2\n+title: \"Trim predicted PC alignment bits\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor work shows the current stateless JAL-taken plus backward-branch-taken policy is the only durable control-flow win. Attempts to add BHT, RAS, JALR memo, loop-exit learning, richer static direction, target sharing, JAL gating, or fall-through rewrites mostly lost Fmax. The safest remaining predictor angle is therefore to keep the exact policy and reduce only the metadata/control cost around predictor repair.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Carry only pred_next_pc[31:2] through IF/ID and ID/EX, because this RV32IM core has no compressed extension and all architecturally valid fetch PCs are word-aligned. IF still computes the same predicted next PC for its local PC update, while EX reconstructs or compares the aligned high bits when checking resolved_next_pc against the prediction. Misaligned branch or jump targets already trap and use pc+4 as the resolved next PC, so the low two predicted bits are redundant for legal retirement and RVFI pc_wdata remains driven from the resolved next PC.\n+\n+  This preserves the proven prediction behavior and all redirect timing semantics, unlike the failed direction-bit rewrite that forced EX to recompute predictor targets. The expected benefit is small but low-risk: two fewer carried predictor bits in early pipeline payloads and a slightly narrower predictor-repair compare, with no new tables, tags, target muxes, or update state.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Narrow the IF/ID and ID/EX predicted-next-PC metadata to aligned high bits while keeping resolved pc_next/RVFI fields full width.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep the existing static JAL/backward-branch predictor policy, but export only the aligned predicted PC high bits after computing the local next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the narrowed predicted-PC metadata through decode without changing instruction decode, register source metadata, or validity handling.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare the resolved aligned next PC against the carried predicted high bits for redirects while preserving misalignment trap behavior and full-width pc_next reporting.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.