, because this RV32IM core has no compressed extension and all architecturally valid fetch PCs are word-aligned. IF still computes the same predicted next PC for its local PC update, while EX reconstructs or compares the aligned high bits when checking resolved_next_pc against the prediction. Misaligned branch or jump targets already trap and use pc+4 as the resolved next PC, so the low two predicted bits are redundant for legal retirement and RVFI pc_wdata remains driven from the resolved next PC.\\n\\nThis preserves the proven prediction behavior and all redirect timing semantics, unlike the failed direction-bit rewrite that forced EX to recompute predictor targets. The expected benefit is small but low-risk: two fewer carried predictor bits in early pipeline payloads and a slightly narrower predictor-repair compare, with no new tables, tags, target muxes, or update state.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta...","metadata":{"matches":5,"truncated":false},"title":"hyp-20260512-003-r12s2|hyp-20260512-003-r10s2|hyp-20260512-003-r11s2|hyp-20260512-003-r13s2|hyp-20260512-003-r14s2","time":{"start":1778635172662,"end":1778635172670}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0287e6321648d158016a03d1a48c4c819892f0ae48acbbfc75"}},"id":"prt_e1eeaeb2e001t1llIzbmZJy50D","sessionID":"ses_1e11580c0ffeSwchj8aKCTzhE6","messageID":"msg_e1eeac20a001VpTmyrduiUKdTe"}}
