{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778620022867,"sessionID":"ses_1e1fcda35ffe8lMIP1geBX0Mjr","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_vq8hCRys9j5m9CHKGyihcw4s","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Static backward branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core fetches sequentially until EX resolves every taken\n+  branch or jump, so tight CoreMark loops pay a two-stage redirect bubble on\n+  each taken back-edge. CoreMark has many small counted loops where a simple\n+  static backward-taken, forward-not-taken predictor should remove most loop\n+  back-edge redirects while keeping LUT and Fmax cost low.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a lightweight fetch-side static predictor that decodes imem_data enough to\n+  compute immediate targets for direct JAL and conditional BRANCH instructions.\n+  Predict JAL taken unconditionally, predict conditional branches taken only\n+  when their B-immediate is negative, and carry the predicted next PC through the\n+  pipeline. In EX, compare the resolved next PC against the predicted next PC\n+  and redirect only on mismatch. This should reduce CoreMark cycles by avoiding\n+  flushes on hot loop back-edges without adding a BTB or saturating counters on\n+  the critical path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 7\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID, ID/EX, and EX/MEM bundles so retirement RVFI pc_wdata still reports the resolved architectural next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Decode direct branch and JAL immediates in fetch, choose the static predicted next PC, and expose prediction metadata while preserving reset, stall, and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch prediction metadata into ID/EX alongside the decoded instruction without changing decoder legality rules.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Resolve actual next PC, flag redirect only when it differs from the carried prediction, and keep misalignment traps and RVFI pc_next semantics intact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat EX misprediction redirects like existing redirects so wrong-path IF and ID instructions are bubbled, while correctly predicted taken branches avoid the flush.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Static backward branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core fetches sequentially until EX resolves every taken\n+  branch or jump, so tight CoreMark loops pay a two-stage redirect bubble on\n+  each taken back-edge. CoreMark has many small counted loops where a simple\n+  static backward-taken, forward-not-taken predictor should remove most loop\n+  back-edge redirects while keeping LUT and Fmax cost low.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a lightweight fetch-side static predictor that decodes imem_data enough to\n+  compute immediate targets for direct JAL and conditional BRANCH instructions.\n+  Predict JAL taken unconditionally, predict conditional branches taken only\n+  when their B-immediate is negative, and carry the predicted next PC through the\n+  pipeline. In EX, compare the resolved next PC against the predicted next PC\n+  and redirect only on mismatch. This should reduce CoreMark cycles by avoiding\n+  flushes on hot loop back-edges without adding a BTB or saturating counters on\n+  the critical path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 7\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID, ID/EX, and EX/MEM bundles so retirement RVFI pc_wdata still reports the resolved architectural next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Decode direct branch and JAL immediates in fetch, choose the static predicted next PC, and expose prediction metadata while preserving reset, stall, and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch prediction metadata into ID/EX alongside the decoded instruction without changing decoder legality rules.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Resolve actual next PC, flag redirect only when it differs from the carried prediction, and keep misalignment traps and RVFI pc_next semantics intact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat EX misprediction redirects like existing redirects so wrong-path IF and ID instructions are bubbled, while correctly predicted taken branches avoid the flush.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2