{"type":"text","timestamp":1778623828923,"sessionID":"ses_1e1c2c6e4ffec4h6DJRi4ryzMu","part":{"id":"prt_e1e3dd34c0011JK2y3jB8Pu6k3","messageID":"msg_e1e3d7327001zT7ridb8kiq5Qq","sessionID":"ses_1e1c2c6e4ffec4h6DJRi4ryzMu","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts show the winning predictor is the current stateless direct-control predictor; the failed variants added IF-stage state. I’m writing a narrower predictor hypothesis that keeps the fetch path stateless and only refines static conditional-branch direction by opcode/funct3.","time":{"start":1778623828812,"end":1778623828922},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0239f302878c103c016a03a554b33481998a8396176eb15778","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778623834449,"sessionID":"ses_1e1c2c6e4ffec4h6DJRi4ryzMu","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_oP8UvdvPQBOHyeiWW6FEq82D","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r4s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r4s2\n+title: \"Refine static branch direction\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current predictor's biggest proven win is its stateless JAL plus backward-branch rule, while the recent RAS and tagged BHT attempts regressed from extra IF-stage state and muxing. CoreMark still pays occasional redirect bubbles when the coarse \"all backward branches taken\" rule is wrong, especially on non-loop backward conditionals and loop-exit forms that use equality compares.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the existing fetch-side target computation and pred_next_pc plumbing, but make conditional branch direction a slightly richer static heuristic using funct3. Predict backward BNE and signed/unsigned range-test branches taken as loop back-edges, keep forward branches not taken, and make backward BEQ fall through by default because equality branches are more often exits/error checks than hot loop latches in optimized CoreMark. This targets remaining static mispredicts without adding tables, tags, RAS state, or EX-to-IF predictor update wiring, so the Fmax risk should be much lower than the failed dynamic predictor attempts.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Refine the static conditional branch predictor to use funct3-specific direction heuristics while preserving the existing JAL prediction and direct target computation.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r4s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_