{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778626138699,"sessionID":"ses_1e19faa87ffec200lzK0gipzQm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_9SvuLZDcRr836AhYvJ5U6Zdm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Learn one hot loop exit\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best predictor is the stateless JAL plus backward-branch rule, which\n+  removes most hot loop back-edge bubbles but still misses the final fall-through\n+  exit of fixed-count backward loops. Prior predictor attempts regressed because\n+  they added general IF-stage tables, tags, RAS state, or indirect-target muxing.\n+  CoreMark has stable counted loops, so a very narrow loop-exit predictor may\n+  recover a recurring miss class without paying the cost of a BHT or BTB.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry learned loop-exit predictor for one hot backward conditional\n+  branch. Keep the existing static direct-control predictor as the default: JAL is\n+  taken and backward branches are taken. On resolved backward branches, IF-side\n+  predictor state learns one PC and its observed taken-run length before a\n+  not-taken exit. When the same branch is fetched on a later run and the local\n+  iteration counter reaches the learned exit count, override the static\n+  backward-taken prediction to fall through; all other branches use the current\n+  low-cost static rule. EX still compares resolved_next_pc against pred_next_pc,\n+  so stale or aliasing predictor state only causes ordinary redirects and cannot\n+  affect RVFI ordering or architectural pc_wdata.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add single-entry backward-loop trip-count state, use it only as a fall-through override for the existing static backward branch prediction, and update it from resolved branch outcomes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose resolved conditional-branch update metadata: valid branch, branch PC, backward offset classification, and actual taken outcome.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the EX-stage branch-update signals back to IF without changing the NRET=1 top-level IO or RVFI channel-0 retirement contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,31 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Learn one hot loop exit\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best predictor is the stateless JAL plus backward-branch rule, which\n+  removes most hot loop back-edge bubbles but still misses the final fall-through\n+  exit of fixed-count backward loops. Prior predictor attempts regressed because\n+  they added general IF-stage tables, tags, RAS state, or indirect-target muxing.\n+  CoreMark has stable counted loops, so a very narrow loop-exit predictor may\n+  recover a recurring miss class without paying the cost of a BHT or BTB.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry learned loop-exit predictor for one hot backward conditional\n+  branch. Keep the existing static direct-control predictor as the default: JAL is\n+  taken and backward branches are taken. On resolved backward bra