{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778628383570,"sessionID":"ses_1e17dbd49ffe1FX7dbvAmBfwQ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ofTNf5jMsXRazhjKIPvLiT3s","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Encode static prediction as direction\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best predictor is the simple stateless rule: predict direct JAL\n+  taken and backward conditional branches taken. Prior predictor attempts that\n+  added BHTs, RAS/JALR state, loop counters, or extra IF target muxing all\n+  regressed, so the next predictor hypothesis should preserve that proven policy\n+  and reduce its implementation cost instead of adding new prediction behavior.\n+\n+  Today IF carries a full 32-bit pred_next_pc through IF/ID and ID/EX only so EX\n+  can compare it with the resolved next PC. For this predictor, correctness only\n+  depends on whether fetch predicted the direct control transfer taken or\n+  fall-through: EX can recompute the same direct JAL/branch target from pc and imm\n+  when needed, and JALR is still predicted fall-through.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the carried pred_next_pc metadata with a compact prediction-direction\n+  bit for the existing static predictor. IF still computes the predicted next PC\n+  locally to update the fetch PC, but it exports only whether it predicted a\n+  direct JAL/backward branch as taken. ID passes that bit to EX. EX compares the\n+  resolved control-flow direction against the carried prediction bit and redirects\n+  only on mismatch, using its already-computed resolved_next_pc as the repair\n+  target.\n+\n+  This keeps the successful JAL-always-taken and backward-branch-taken policy\n+  unchanged while removing a 32-bit predicted-PC field from early pipeline\n+  registers and eliminating a 32-bit resolved_next_pc != pred_next_pc comparator\n+  on the EX redirect path. It should slightly improve Fmax and routing pressure\n+  without adding predictor state, changing RVFI pc_wdata, changing NRET=1 IO, or\n+  weakening illegal-instruction redirect repair.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the 32-bit pred_next_pc fields in IF/ID and ID/EX with a compact predicted-taken direction bit for the existing static predictor.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep the current static JAL/backward-branch PC selection, but export only the prediction direction bit instead of a full predicted next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate the prediction direction bit through the ID/EX register without changing decode legality or RVFI source metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Redirect on resolved direction mismatch using the existing resolved_next_pc repair target, including illegal or misaligned cases that must fall through.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,42 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Encode static prediction as direction\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best predictor is the simple stateless rule: predict direc